How to change the color of a span tag on mouse over? I'm trying this, but it doesn't work:

$("span").mouseover(function(){
  $(this).css("color","#00ff00");
}).mouseout(function(){
  $(this).css("color","#000000");
});

The code works fine for changing the color back when the mouse leaves the element, but not when the mouse is over it. As far as I can tell, the code is correct.

Answer: You need to use `hover` instead of `mouseover`. Here's an example:

\begin{code}
$("span").hover(function() {
  $(this).css("color", "#00ff00");
}, function() {
  $(this).css("color", "#000000");
});
\end{code}

